<item>
            <title>[LU-17230] socklnd: treat UNKNOWN netif operational state as UP rather than DOWN</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17230</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&quot;UNKNOWN&quot; (IF_OPER_UNKNOWN) operational state doesn&apos;t necessarily mean that the interface can&apos;t be used and may be the result of particular network driver not providing UP/DOWN states, so it may be incorrect for socklnd to initiate setting of a &quot;fatal error&quot; flag on a NI using an interface in &quot;UNKNOWN&quot; operstate.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
